{
    "question": "Fill in the blank: In both Redis and MongoDB, the primary key is a crucial part of the data structure, determining how data is stored and accessed. Given the following pseudo-code depiction of data insertion in both databases, what should replace the blanks to define the primary key?\n```python\n# Redis\nredis_db.set(______, 'value')\n\n# MongoDB\ndata = {'_id': ______, 'content': 'data'}\nmongo_db.collection.insert_one(data)\n```",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "\"primary\", \"primary\"",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "\"key\", \"_id\"",
            "correct": "true"
        },
        {
            "choice": "\"data\", \"data\"",
            "correct": "false"
        }
    ]
}

